column4: <content>Conversion of St. Paul: of great importance for composition: The Albertina drawing of the Way to Calvary. Generally: Way to Calvary composition contains the germ of the composition with the place of execution (= paralleled by place of Saul's fall) in the distance to which the procession is moving cf. e.g. Aertsen (Lucas Galerie) 1553 and in others.</content>
